  - set reconciliation
  - machine epistemics
abstract: >-
  abductor externalizes the test so an LLM has to represent the rule instead of
  tabulating the example. It enumerates a fixpoint-closed space of cases for the
  property under repair, calibrates each against a known-good baseline so every
  case carries external ground truth, and exposes one pass/fail gate the model
  hill-climbs against. The gate's coverage, not the model's prior, sets the
  generalization frontier, and the search records itself as a replayable
  hypothesis graph (fixes as nodes, counterexamples as edges). Tooling behind the
  paper "The Hypothesis Graph: Semantic Memory Written by Methodeutics".
